# Naming Conventions

## Files & Folders
- **Folders**: `kebab-case` (e.g. `fact-sheet`, `pipeline-run`, `agent-worker`)
- **React components**: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `ProjectCard.tsx`, `StoryboardViewer.tsx`, `PipelineStatus.tsx`)
- **Non-component TypeScript**: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g. `fact-sheet.ts`, `pipeline-runner.ts`, `name-registry.ts`)
- **API routes**: `kebab-case.ts` in Express router files (e.g. `projects.ts`, `pipeline.ts`)
- **Types files**: `kebab-case.ts` in `src/types/` (e.g. `project.ts`, `fact-sheet.ts`, `pipeline.ts`)

## Exports
- **React components**: named export using `PascalCase` function declaration (e.g. `export function ProjectCard()`)
- **Hooks**: named export prefixed with `use` (e.g. `export function useProject()`)
- **Utility functions**: named export using `camelCase` (e.g. `export function validateFactSheet()`)
- **Constants**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `AGENT_TIMEOUT_MS`, `PIPELINE_STAGES`, `MAX_RETRIES`)
- **Types/interfaces**: `PascalCase` (e.g. `FactSheet`, `PipelineRun`, `AgentOutput`)
- **Zod schemas**: `camelCase` suffixed with `Schema` (e.g. `factSheetSchema`, `agentOutputSchema`)

## Component Files
- One primary component per file
- File name matches the exported component name
- Internal sub-components stay in the same file — don't extract unless reused

## Import Style
- Always use path alias `@/...` — never relative `../../` imports
- Relative imports (`./`) only for sibling files in the same directory
- Group imports: external packages → `@/` aliases → relative `./` — separated by blank lines
